main event: A cone-shaped object with a rounded leading edge, 6-8 inches in diameter, was observed drifting with a tinge of ultraviolet between Vinton and Oelwein, Iowa on August 21, 1958.
interesting points: The object was bright with a red or black ring of lights around the middle, and was initially invisible to the naked eye.
The object moved at a moderate speed from north-northeast to south-southwest.
The brightness of the object varied, with it becoming obscured behind clouds at times.
The report concludes that the object was possibly a balloon, but the data was insufficient for a full evaluation.
The sighting lasted for approximately 45 minutes.
sighted object: cone-shaped object with a rounded leading edge
